9.2 What This Simulation Supports
A strong, transparent case for hardware validation — the projected efficiency gain is large enough (multiple orders of magnitude) to remain compelling even under conservative re-estimation.
A specific, concrete ask: one independent benchmark run on Snapdragon hardware, in partnership with Qualcomm AI Research, to close the gap between this simulation and a physical result.
A fully open, reproducible method — anyone can inspect, run, and challenge the simulation model itself using the repository code.
9.3 The Verification Principle, Stated Honestly
For a deterministic architecture, a cycle-accurate simulation built from a stated hardware specification can compute exact, reproducible outputs — for the model. That is a genuine methodological strength: there's no statistical noise to explain away. It is not, however, a substitute for a physical measurement, and this paper does not claim it is. The specific, falsifiable ask in Section 8.2 exists precisely so that claim can be tested rather than assumed.
